data.meta_desc: Soviet gymnast, Elena Mukhina, was once widely considered as the next great gymnastics star. however, in 1979, she broke a leg and missed several competitions. despite her injuries, her coach rushed her recoveries and pressured her to master a difficult and dangerous tumbling move called the thomas salto.
